WEBVTT

00:10.542 --> 00:12.875
(Ominous music)

00:12.875 --> 00:28.542
♪♪♪

00:28.542 --> 00:30.833
(Crows caw)

00:30.833 --> 00:33.042
Maclaughlan: Don't let the
Irish lad out of your sight.

00:33.042 --> 00:35.500
He's worth five times
your weight in ale.

00:35.500 --> 00:37.417
That's not what I said!

00:37.417 --> 00:38.583
Jesus!

00:38.583 --> 00:41.125
We are here.

00:41.125 --> 00:43.542
We are goin' there.
That's East. That's South.

00:43.542 --> 00:46.208
That's where we're goin'!
Idiot.

00:46.208 --> 00:48.375
♪♪♪

00:48.375 --> 00:49.792
- (Nervous inhale)

00:49.792 --> 00:51.208
(Footsteps crunch)

00:51.208 --> 00:53.750
Harp: (Clears throat)
- (Surprised gasp)

00:53.750 --> 00:55.792
- Declan Harp.

00:55.792 --> 00:58.042
You mad bastard.

00:58.042 --> 01:00.250
- I'm here to negotiate
for the hostage.

01:00.250 --> 01:02.958
- Oh, there'll be no
negotiation.

01:02.958 --> 01:05.500
On the ground,
face down now.

01:05.708 --> 01:13.000
♪♪♪

01:13.000 --> 01:14.875
- Those are pretty hats.

01:17.000 --> 01:18.833
If you release him to me

01:18.833 --> 01:20.792
I might let you keep yours.

01:20.792 --> 01:22.500
- (Laughs)

01:22.500 --> 01:24.083
You've got some stones, Harp,

01:24.083 --> 01:25.542
I'll give you that,

01:25.542 --> 01:29.000
but you're out
of your fuckin' mind.

01:29.000 --> 01:31.417
- Dogs...

01:31.417 --> 01:33.125
wearin' hats.

01:34.083 --> 01:36.875
Maclaughlan: Well, maybe
you donna count so well,

01:36.875 --> 01:38.458
but you're badly outnumbered.

01:38.458 --> 01:40.417
(Sharp thunk)
- (Gurgling grunt)

01:40.417 --> 01:42.375
(Hard thump)
- (Gasping grunt)

01:42.375 --> 01:43.583
(Struggling grunts)

01:43.583 --> 01:45.208
- Good dog.

01:45.208 --> 01:47.292
Michael: (Grunts with effort)

01:47.292 --> 01:48.417
- (Grimacing grunt)

01:48.417 --> 01:49.917
Ah!

01:49.917 --> 01:51.833
Michael: You could help here,
you know!

01:51.833 --> 01:52.583
- (Grimacing grunt)

01:52.583 --> 01:54.583
Harp: Ah ah ah ah ah ah,
let him go.

01:54.583 --> 01:56.042
That's it.
- (Panting grunts)

01:56.042 --> 01:58.208
- Keep the pressure on,
if you let him breathe

01:58.208 --> 02:01.125
you're right back at square one.
- Harp! Help! (Gun clinks)

02:01.125 --> 02:03.125
- What would you do
if I wasn't here?

02:04.458 --> 02:07.500
(Straining gasps)
(Loud grunts)

02:07.500 --> 02:09.500
- (Determined grunts)
- (Fading gasp)

02:09.500 --> 02:14.875
♪♪♪

02:14.875 --> 02:16.833
- (Exhausted grunt) (Loud thump)

02:16.833 --> 02:18.958
- (Gasping for air)
Oh God! Did I kill him?

02:18.958 --> 02:21.167
Harp: No, no, no,
he's just unconscious.

02:21.167 --> 02:23.083
Are you hurt?

02:23.083 --> 02:25.042
- (Sharp whimper)
- Oh no, I'm great.

02:25.042 --> 02:27.417
Just freezin' to death. Thanks.

02:27.417 --> 02:29.417
- (Guttural grunts)
- Go get yourself a coat.

02:29.417 --> 02:31.208
Man: (Choked grunts)

02:31.208 --> 02:32.417
- Help yourself.

02:33.500 --> 02:35.417
(Crows caw)

02:37.417 --> 02:38.417
Now he's dead.

02:38.417 --> 02:40.000
(Sighs)

02:40.000 --> 02:41.750
The Low River Company tartan.

02:41.750 --> 02:44.167
(Bindings snap)

02:44.167 --> 02:45.667
You work for Malcolm Brown?

02:48.250 --> 02:49.292
So you murder innocent
Lake Walkers

02:49.292 --> 02:51.583
and take my man hostage?

02:51.583 --> 02:54.125
- (Spits defiantly)

02:54.125 --> 02:56.500
- Hmm. (Sniffs)

02:56.500 --> 03:02.292
♪♪♪

03:02.292 --> 03:03.667
(Slicing strike)
- Ah!

03:03.667 --> 03:05.750
(Shouts in pain)

03:05.750 --> 03:08.583
- Perhaps you didn't hear me.
- (Grunts in pain)

03:08.583 --> 03:10.542
- I asked if you worked
for Malcolm Brown?

03:10.542 --> 03:12.125
- Fuck you!

03:12.125 --> 03:13.417
(Violent punch)

03:13.417 --> 03:14.792
Fuckin' bastard!

03:14.792 --> 03:16.500
(Crunching stomp)
- (Bellows in pain)

03:16.500 --> 03:19.042
- He murdered Kitchi. Kill him
and let's get on with it.

03:19.042 --> 03:20.833
- Oh no, I'm not gonna be
killing you dog.

03:20.833 --> 03:21.583
Maclaughlan: Damn it!

03:21.583 --> 03:22.833
- You're gonna take me
to Malcolm Brown,

03:22.833 --> 03:23.542
Maclaughlan: My fuckin' ear!

03:23.542 --> 03:25.417
- and I want some answers.
Maclaughlan: Fuck you! Jesus!

03:25.417 --> 03:28.208
- Up dog!
- (Grunts, shouts in pain)

03:28.208 --> 03:30.708
Fuck you! Fuck you!
- Good boy.

03:32.208 --> 03:42.208
♪♪♪

03:44.917 --> 03:47.083
(Native singing)

03:47.083 --> 04:02.167
♪♪♪

04:02.167 --> 04:04.958
(Native singing)

04:04.958 --> 04:17.500
♪♪♪

04:21.417 --> 04:23.208
(Birds chirp)

04:23.208 --> 04:25.417
(Mournful native singing)

04:25.417 --> 04:27.292
♪♪♪

04:27.292 --> 04:29.708
(Feather wafts)

04:29.708 --> 04:31.625
(Mournful native singing)

04:31.625 --> 04:46.958
♪♪♪

04:46.958 --> 04:51.833
♪♪♪

04:53.292 --> 04:58.083
I have gathered a group of men
who are willing to fight.

04:58.083 --> 05:01.208
Kamenna, the people are with me.

05:01.208 --> 05:05.208
They demand justice.

05:07.750 --> 05:13.750
The men who attacked
wore Low River colours.

05:16.125 --> 05:18.500
When Harp returns we'll learn...

05:18.500 --> 05:22.000
Declan Harp can tell us nothing!

05:22.000 --> 05:31.000
He's more like his European
father than us.

05:34.125 --> 05:36.208
- Machk!

05:36.208 --> 05:37.583
(Mournful native singing)

05:37.583 --> 05:41.333
♪♪♪

05:41.333 --> 05:43.250
Dimanche: Why go to
Malcolm Brown?

05:43.250 --> 05:45.208
This is exactly the kind
of reckless move

05:45.208 --> 05:46.792
that got Samoset killed.

05:46.792 --> 05:49.958
- Mind your tongue
or I will cut it out.

05:49.958 --> 05:51.833
- Why not go to Kamenna?

05:51.833 --> 05:54.167
- Machk will demand retaliation
against the Brown Brothers.

05:54.167 --> 05:56.125
He's probably already moving
on the Low River camp.

05:56.125 --> 05:57.417
- Brown is our competition.

05:57.417 --> 05:59.625
Why not let the Lake Walkers
destroy them?

05:59.625 --> 06:03.333
- 'Cause that's what
Benton wants.

06:03.333 --> 06:06.000
Right? If we're out here
killing each other,

06:06.000 --> 06:07.417
it makes it that much easier
for Benton

06:07.417 --> 06:09.375
to tighten his grip on
controlling the trade.

06:09.375 --> 06:11.583
- The HBC is our common enemy.

06:11.583 --> 06:13.125
They have unlimited resources

06:13.125 --> 06:15.083
and if we are gonna take them
and Benton down

06:15.083 --> 06:16.583
we're gonna need all
the independent companies

06:16.583 --> 06:17.708
to work together.

06:17.792 --> 06:19.375
We have to stop this war
between the Browns

06:19.375 --> 06:22.333
and the Lake Walkers
before it happens.

06:22.333 --> 06:23.333
Let's go.

06:24.833 --> 06:26.833
Up!

06:26.833 --> 06:28.333
- (Muffled grimaces)

06:29.583 --> 06:31.250
(Footsteps crunch in the snow)

06:31.250 --> 06:32.708
(Low hum of chatter)

06:32.708 --> 06:36.750
Coffin: Oh God, whose attribute
is always to have mercy

06:38.208 --> 06:40.000
and to uh... to spare,

06:41.292 --> 06:42.958
we uh...

06:42.958 --> 06:44.917
- Ach, get on with it, man.

06:44.917 --> 06:46.500
Coffin: We humbly present
our prayers to thee

06:46.500 --> 06:48.500
for the souls of thy loyal
servants whom thou uh,

06:48.500 --> 06:51.417
whom thou hast called...
- Declan Harp.

06:51.417 --> 06:53.792
Coffin: ...has this day called
out of this world...

06:53.792 --> 06:56.667
- How in God's name did you let
him kill so many of our men?

06:56.667 --> 06:58.792
- We were taken by surprise.

06:58.792 --> 07:01.750
- He knew exactly where to find
the Lake Walker boy.

07:01.750 --> 07:03.958
Coffin: ...into the hands
of the enemy, nor to,

07:03.958 --> 07:06.667
nor to forget forever,
but to, to...

07:06.667 --> 07:08.667
- You dispatched Cedric Brown,
did you not?

07:08.667 --> 07:10.667
- I did. I stabbed him myself.

07:10.667 --> 07:13.542
- Did Harp see you kill him,
see you take the child?

07:13.542 --> 07:14.833
- No, it's impossible.

07:14.833 --> 07:16.708
Coffin: ...to-to bear them
into paradise, yes!

07:16.708 --> 07:19.083
- Would you shut up
for one moment!

07:19.083 --> 07:20.792
- (Relieved sigh)

07:20.792 --> 07:22.667
- Chesterfield, remind me,

07:22.667 --> 07:25.333
where did you find young Kitchi?

07:25.333 --> 07:26.792
Chesterfield?

07:30.583 --> 07:32.583
- In the storeroom behind
the ale house.

07:32.583 --> 07:39.375
♪♪♪

07:39.375 --> 07:42.000
(Seagulls cry,
townspeople chatter)

07:42.000 --> 07:43.917
(Patrons laugh
and chatter loudly)

07:43.917 --> 07:45.000
(Door opens)

07:47.083 --> 07:49.000
(Patrons stop talking)

07:50.792 --> 07:52.667
- Leave.

07:52.667 --> 07:54.250
(Chairs scrapping,
scrambling footsteps)

07:54.250 --> 07:59.875
♪♪♪

07:59.875 --> 08:01.542
Emberly!

08:01.542 --> 08:08.333
♪♪♪

08:08.333 --> 08:10.042
(Door squeaks shut)

08:10.042 --> 08:12.000
- Lord Benton.

08:16.208 --> 08:17.708
Can I offer you somethin'?

08:17.708 --> 08:20.000
(Sucks his teeth)

08:20.000 --> 08:22.125
- Brandy.

08:22.125 --> 08:23.708
- Of course.

08:24.917 --> 08:27.000
- Something has come
to my attention

08:27.000 --> 08:28.500
which is very troubling.

08:28.500 --> 08:29.833
- Oh?

08:31.167 --> 08:33.708
What's that, my Lord?

08:33.708 --> 08:35.750
- The Lake Walker boy.

08:35.750 --> 08:39.125
You did not inform me
that he was in your care.

08:39.125 --> 08:41.583
- I dinna wish to waste
your time

08:41.583 --> 08:44.792
given your new responsibilities
as acting governor

08:44.792 --> 08:46.958
since Mr. Threadwell's
untimely death.

08:51.833 --> 08:53.917
- Sparing me the trouble.

08:53.917 --> 08:55.708
Hmm, how thoughtful.

08:56.833 --> 08:59.500
- Exactly, my Lord.

08:59.500 --> 09:02.167
Benton: You've fared well
with this place,

09:02.167 --> 09:04.875
a woman, amongst all these
rough men.

09:04.875 --> 09:07.833
One might even say
you prospered,

09:07.833 --> 09:11.167
but I need hardly remind you
that your ale house

09:11.167 --> 09:13.750
operates by license
and with my blessing.

09:18.667 --> 09:21.750
- Of course, my Lord,
I am at your service,

09:21.750 --> 09:23.750
but without hot food and drink

09:23.750 --> 09:25.750
you might have a mutiny
on your hands.

09:25.750 --> 09:28.792
- Oh, I'd never close
the place, my dear,

09:28.792 --> 09:32.000
I'd simply award the license
to someone else,

09:32.000 --> 09:34.458
someone who fits more
comfortably in britches.

09:38.125 --> 09:39.958
I have reason to believe

09:39.958 --> 09:43.083
that you've been entertaining
Declan Harp,

09:43.083 --> 09:44.917
feeding him information.

09:46.125 --> 09:49.250
- I have na seen Declan Harp
in years,

09:49.250 --> 09:52.708
and I certainly wouldn't
allow him in here, my Lord.

09:52.708 --> 09:54.167
- No, of course not.

09:55.375 --> 09:57.250
(Sipping)

09:57.250 --> 09:59.750
Hmm, this is excellent brandy.

10:00.250 --> 10:02.667
It's French, isn't it?

10:03.875 --> 10:05.833
- Yes, my Lord.

10:05.833 --> 10:07.750
- Such a pity it's illegal.

10:09.208 --> 10:12.792
The black market does carry
risks, Miss Emberly.

10:12.792 --> 10:14.542
Chesterfield...

10:15.750 --> 10:18.000
search the premises.

10:18.000 --> 10:21.792
Any barrel, cask or bottle that
does not have the HBC stamp,

10:21.792 --> 10:24.583
remove at once.
(Cup clanks down)

10:24.583 --> 10:26.375
(Receding footsteps)

10:27.667 --> 10:29.000
(Door opens and closes)

10:29.000 --> 10:30.500
(Bottles clank)

10:30.500 --> 10:31.833
- What the hell is goin' on?

10:31.833 --> 10:34.125
- I'll get this under control.

10:34.125 --> 10:37.125
- We need to move those pelts.

10:37.125 --> 10:39.208
- Yeah.

10:39.208 --> 10:40.958
(Crate creaks)

10:44.500 --> 10:46.625
(Fire crackles, men chatter)

10:46.625 --> 10:48.542
(Footsteps crunch in the snow)

10:49.750 --> 10:51.583
(Muskets click)

10:52.792 --> 10:54.583
- Where is he?

10:56.000 --> 10:58.417
Stay here. Stay alert.

10:58.417 --> 11:01.250
(Footsteps crunch in the snow)

11:01.250 --> 11:02.750
(Men chatter)

11:05.708 --> 11:07.458
(Canvas rustles loudly)

11:11.042 --> 11:15.167
- Declan fuckin' Harp
in the flesh.

11:15.167 --> 11:16.750
You'd better tell me
why the fuck

11:16.750 --> 11:19.042
you're walking around my camp
like you own the fuckin' place.

11:19.042 --> 11:21.250
- Oh I found this piece of shit

11:21.250 --> 11:23.292
and I thought you might
want it back.

11:23.292 --> 11:25.792
On your fuckin' knees!
- (Muffled grunts of pain)

11:25.792 --> 11:28.250
- Huh. Maclaughlan.

11:28.250 --> 11:30.917
- Does he work for you?
- This fuckin' thief?

11:30.917 --> 11:33.417
I threw him and some other
useless pricks like him

11:33.417 --> 11:34.417
out months ago.

11:34.417 --> 11:37.208
I'd sooner gut him than
look at him.

11:38.417 --> 11:40.042
What did he do?

11:40.042 --> 11:43.208
- Attacked the Lake Walker
village, half a dozen dead.

11:43.208 --> 11:45.375
- Jesus Christ.

11:45.375 --> 11:48.042
Fuckin' idiot!

11:48.042 --> 11:50.125
- (Grimaces in pain)
- He's wearin' your colors.

11:50.125 --> 11:52.833
- So that's why you're here,

11:52.833 --> 11:54.917
to accuse me of murder?

11:54.917 --> 11:57.458
- Is that how you would
do business, eh?

11:57.458 --> 11:59.917
Kill your suppliers?
(Snorts)

11:59.917 --> 12:01.875
Don't be ridiculous, man.

12:01.875 --> 12:04.333
- Yeah, well, your fuckhead
brother kidnapped one of them.

12:04.333 --> 12:05.917
Kitchi...

12:05.917 --> 12:08.333
the Okimaw's grandson?
Held him hostage.

12:08.333 --> 12:09.917
- If Cedric had anythin'
to do with this

12:09.917 --> 12:11.667
I'll personally rip him
a new arse!

12:11.667 --> 12:13.042
- Cedric's dead.

12:14.917 --> 12:16.708
A man named Chesterfield,

12:16.708 --> 12:19.500
Lord Benton's right hand man.

12:22.250 --> 12:23.500
- (Angry exhale)

12:24.833 --> 12:27.167
I'm gonna find this man
Chesterfield,

12:27.167 --> 12:28.417
and when I'm finished with him

12:28.417 --> 12:30.667
there won't be a piece
bigger than my fist!

12:30.667 --> 12:32.958
- You got a bigger problem,
Brown.

12:32.958 --> 12:34.958
The Lake Walkers
are seeking retribution.

12:34.958 --> 12:37.125
- I know nothing about
no fuckin' attack!

12:37.125 --> 12:38.208
Why would I murder them?

12:38.208 --> 12:39.917
I need their fucking trade!

12:41.542 --> 12:42.708
You...

12:42.708 --> 12:44.292
who told you to do it, hey?

12:44.292 --> 12:46.333
(Violent blow)
- (Grunts in pain)

12:46.333 --> 12:49.083
(Kicking viciously)
Who fuckin' hired ya?!

12:49.083 --> 12:51.458
Answer me or I swear to Christ

12:51.458 --> 12:53.583
I'll rip your head
from your fuckin' body!

12:53.583 --> 12:54.875
(Violent crunching blow)

12:54.875 --> 12:56.875
- He's not gonna talk.

12:56.875 --> 12:58.958
You'll need to talk
to the Lake Walkers.

12:58.958 --> 13:00.958
You tell them you didn't do
this, otherwise who knows.

13:00.958 --> 13:03.000
(Booming musket shot)
Man: Savages!

13:03.000 --> 13:04.042
(Men shout and scream,
muskets boom)

13:04.042 --> 13:06.000
- All right.
Man: We're under attack!

13:06.000 --> 13:07.000
(Muskets boom, men shout)

13:07.000 --> 13:09.667
(Panicked shouting)

13:09.667 --> 13:11.667
- Lake Walkers,
shooting from the forest!

13:11.667 --> 13:13.875
(Loud musket shot)
- Ach, come on!

13:13.875 --> 13:16.542
Man: Oh, I've been hit! -
Somebody give me a musket!

13:16.542 --> 13:18.458
- He claims he didn't order
the killings.

13:18.458 --> 13:19.583
- You believe him?

13:19.583 --> 13:21.250
- This is Benton's work.

13:21.250 --> 13:23.542
It's what he wants,
us at each other's throats.

13:23.542 --> 13:25.542
We need proof for
Kamenna to stop Machk.

13:27.292 --> 13:28.958
- I could free Maclaughlan,

13:28.958 --> 13:30.417
let him escape and follow him.

13:30.417 --> 13:31.667
If we're right,

13:31.667 --> 13:33.792
he'll lead us straight
to Benton.

13:33.792 --> 13:36.125
- All right, do it.
Take Michael with you.

13:36.125 --> 13:37.833
- He'll slow me down!

13:37.833 --> 13:39.750
- So teach him.

13:39.750 --> 13:41.667
Dimanche, with me!

13:41.667 --> 13:43.833
- (Men shout, muskets boom)

13:43.833 --> 13:45.833
- Man: Look out!
- Ahh!

13:45.833 --> 13:47.792
- Look out!
(Muskets boom)

13:49.083 --> 13:50.583
(Blade clangs)

13:52.167 --> 13:54.083
(Binding snap)

13:54.083 --> 13:57.167
- Run, before I change my mind.

13:57.167 --> 13:58.708
- (Panicked breathing)

13:58.708 --> 14:00.583
(Muskets boom, men shout)

14:01.875 --> 14:03.208
- We're goin' after him, right?

14:03.208 --> 14:05.375
- You're going to do
exactly as I say.

14:05.375 --> 14:09.083
Man: We need to get
in formation, quick!

14:09.083 --> 14:13.083
(Hooves clatter,
people chatter in French)

14:13.333 --> 14:14.875
(Footsteps thud)

14:19.083 --> 14:21.583
- Mr. Pond, make yourself
at home.

14:23.250 --> 14:25.375
- Mr. Grant would like a word.

14:26.875 --> 14:30.208
- And I'd like you to get out
from behind my bloody desk.

14:31.708 --> 14:33.083
- (Grunts)

14:35.375 --> 14:37.083
I have a carriage waiting.

14:38.375 --> 14:40.125
- You may tell your employer

14:40.125 --> 14:43.625
that I donna have time
to see him today.

14:43.625 --> 14:46.708
- Actually, I believe you have
time right now.

14:46.708 --> 14:48.250
(Gun cocks)

14:48.250 --> 14:50.708
(Classical music)

14:50.708 --> 14:58.333
♪♪♪

14:58.333 --> 14:59.667
(Birds chirping)

15:00.958 --> 15:02.917
- Langmead and Langmead,
Lemont Furs,

15:04.375 --> 15:05.958
Levesque and Sons.

15:05.958 --> 15:07.583
You are familiar with
these companies?

15:07.583 --> 15:09.750
- Aye, so?

15:09.750 --> 15:12.708
- So each of them are illegally
conducting trade in the North

15:12.708 --> 15:15.083
in territory granted
to the Hudson's Bay Company,

15:15.083 --> 15:16.917
just as you are.

15:16.917 --> 15:20.208
The most successful is a man
named Peter Carruthers,

15:20.208 --> 15:21.708
Carruthers and Co.
You know him?

15:21.708 --> 15:23.208
- What if I do?

15:23.208 --> 15:24.708
- You are to speak with him.

15:24.708 --> 15:27.792
You will invite him here
tomorrow afternoon.

15:27.792 --> 15:30.000
- Carruthers is my direct
competition.

15:30.000 --> 15:32.333
Why would I invite him here
to speak with you?

15:32.333 --> 15:34.500
- Because I'm asking you nicely.

15:36.167 --> 15:38.125
I'd do it myself,
but I'm new in town

15:38.125 --> 15:39.375
and we're not yet acquainted.

15:40.917 --> 15:44.917
- I think, Mr. Grant,
that you misunderstand

15:45.208 --> 15:47.083
the nature of our dealings.

15:47.083 --> 15:48.083
- (Laughs)

15:49.292 --> 15:51.042
(Newspaper rustles)

15:52.583 --> 15:54.417
I loan you money;

15:54.417 --> 15:56.292
you travel North;

15:56.292 --> 15:58.042
you trade;

15:58.042 --> 16:00.917
you return home with furs
and you give them to me,

16:00.917 --> 16:03.333
at which point the debt
is repaid.

16:03.333 --> 16:05.375
If, in the meantime,

16:05.375 --> 16:08.000
I ask you for a favor
and you oblige,

16:08.000 --> 16:09.583
well, Mr. Brown, that's...

16:09.583 --> 16:11.750
that's just good business.

16:11.750 --> 16:14.750
Otherwise, I might be tempted
to demand immediate repayment,

16:14.750 --> 16:17.042
which of course would land you
in debtor's prison

16:17.042 --> 16:18.792
and from what I understand...

16:18.792 --> 16:20.917
it's rather unpleasant.

16:22.958 --> 16:24.458
Mr. Carruthers.

16:24.458 --> 16:26.583
Here tomorrow.

16:26.583 --> 16:35.167
♪♪♪

16:35.167 --> 16:36.750
- Goodbye, Mr. Brown.

16:36.750 --> 16:40.833
♪♪♪

16:40.833 --> 16:43.125
(Snow scrapes)

16:43.125 --> 16:45.292
(Low hum of chatter)

16:45.292 --> 16:47.208
- Four men dead.

16:47.208 --> 16:50.167
All well trained,
tough-as-nails highlanders.

16:50.167 --> 16:52.000
- This is revenge.

16:52.000 --> 16:53.417
- I did nothing.

16:53.417 --> 16:55.958
They are gonna fuckin' pay
for this.

16:55.958 --> 16:59.000
- You're in their territory
and you're vastly outnumbered.

16:59.000 --> 17:01.208
- You don't know what my men
are capable of.

17:01.208 --> 17:03.375
Dimanche: How quickly can they
dig their own graves?

17:03.375 --> 17:05.417
Both: (Grunt)
(Hard thump)

17:05.417 --> 17:07.792
- (Grunts)
- This ends now.

17:07.792 --> 17:10.667
You are not getting into
a war with Lake Walkers.

17:10.667 --> 17:12.542
I'm trying to help you.

17:12.542 --> 17:14.750
- Aye, that's what
it feels like.

17:14.750 --> 17:16.750
- I'm offering you
the opportunity

17:16.750 --> 17:18.250
to take revenge against the man

17:18.250 --> 17:20.292
who murdered your brother
in cold blood.

17:20.292 --> 17:22.583
Chesterfield,

17:22.583 --> 17:24.667
the HBC,
that is the real enemy.

17:24.667 --> 17:26.625
- (Grunts)

17:26.625 --> 17:29.250
(Pants)

17:29.250 --> 17:31.333
- You will speak to the Okimaw.

17:31.333 --> 17:34.250
You will tell her that you did
not attack her people

17:34.250 --> 17:36.500
and you will make peace.

17:36.500 --> 17:39.542
If you do not, you and your men
will all die.

17:39.542 --> 17:54.750
♪♪♪

17:54.750 --> 17:56.542
- (Breathing hard)

17:57.792 --> 17:59.625
(Footsteps crunch in the snow)

18:01.833 --> 18:03.167
He's stopped.

18:03.167 --> 18:04.500
- Oh, a fire!

18:04.500 --> 18:06.375
Can we light one, too?
I'm freezin'.

18:06.375 --> 18:07.708
- No.

18:07.708 --> 18:09.292
(Exhales)

18:09.292 --> 18:11.750
He's already paranoid.
See there?

18:11.750 --> 18:13.708
He twists a little.

18:13.708 --> 18:16.333
He was looking over
his shoulder as he walked.

18:16.333 --> 18:18.750
- I don't suppose you know
how to build a fire

18:18.750 --> 18:20.708
that doesn't make smoke.

18:20.708 --> 18:22.833
(Inhales and blows)

18:24.250 --> 18:26.458
- Press up your body
against mine.

18:26.458 --> 18:27.958
- What?

18:27.958 --> 18:29.292
(Footsteps shuttle)

18:30.375 --> 18:32.125
(Wind gusts)

18:32.125 --> 18:33.333
(Exhales)

18:33.333 --> 18:34.542
Oh.

18:35.667 --> 18:37.792
(Clears throat)

18:37.792 --> 18:39.583
(Wind howls)

18:39.583 --> 18:41.708
(Bird cries)

18:41.708 --> 18:44.083
- You miss London?

18:45.917 --> 18:49.000
- I miss some things about it,
sure. (Sniffs)

18:49.000 --> 18:51.250
It's not an easy place to live,
London,

18:51.250 --> 18:54.500
(Sighs)

18:54.500 --> 18:56.708
but I had Clenna. Tom.

18:58.625 --> 19:00.625
She's an amazing person, Clenna.

19:02.625 --> 19:04.583
Beautiful,
smart as a bloody whip,

19:05.375 --> 19:07.083
never let me get away
with shite.

19:07.083 --> 19:09.083
(Sniffs)

19:09.083 --> 19:11.750
Once, we broke into
this fancy house

19:11.750 --> 19:13.708
and she tried on this lady's
silk dress.

19:13.708 --> 19:15.708
(Chuckles)

19:15.708 --> 19:17.458
She was so happy.

19:18.917 --> 19:21.333
I promised her that one day
she'd have a feather bed

19:21.333 --> 19:23.375
and a dress like that
of her own.

19:23.375 --> 19:25.375
We would take walks
in the park

19:25.375 --> 19:27.500
and she'd be wearing her dress

19:27.500 --> 19:29.833
and I'd be wearing a top hat,

19:29.833 --> 19:31.500
eatin' oranges.

19:33.958 --> 19:35.542
- Oranges?

19:37.750 --> 19:39.500
- Oranges.

19:41.583 --> 19:43.125
Fruit.

19:44.375 --> 19:46.750
They're sweet and round and...

19:46.750 --> 19:48.792
orange.

19:48.792 --> 19:50.500
They're full of juice!

19:50.500 --> 19:52.917
You can suck on 'em or eat 'em.

19:52.917 --> 19:54.500
I've never had one before...

19:54.500 --> 19:56.000
(Sighs)

19:56.000 --> 19:57.458
but I will.

19:57.458 --> 20:01.042
- So you miss her because
she looks good in a dress

20:01.042 --> 20:03.708
and you want to wear a top hat

20:03.708 --> 20:04.708
and suck fruit.

20:05.625 --> 20:08.000
- (Chuckles)

20:08.000 --> 20:09.875
Well, when you put it like that
it sounds a little--

20:09.875 --> 20:11.583
- The fire's out!

20:11.583 --> 20:13.542
He's on the move again.

20:13.542 --> 20:16.000
(Footsteps crunch in snow)

20:19.292 --> 20:22.583
Coffin: The brandy you drink is
the devil's brew, my friends,

20:22.583 --> 20:24.667
and it will take you
straight to hell.

20:24.667 --> 20:27.500
You must leave this place
and never return,

20:27.500 --> 20:29.458
and once you are outside
in the street

20:29.458 --> 20:30.833
you must fall on your knees

20:30.833 --> 20:33.042
and beg the forgiveness
of our Lord Jesus Christ!

20:33.042 --> 20:35.042
- Father Coffin,
you must be hungry.

20:35.042 --> 20:36.792
I brought you something to eat.

20:36.792 --> 20:39.042
When was the last time
you had a meal?

20:39.042 --> 20:40.875
- Some time, I'll admit.

20:40.875 --> 20:43.083
- I am reborn, praise God,

20:43.083 --> 20:45.625
and whilst I bask in His glory
I am penniless

20:45.625 --> 20:48.083
and frankly very, very hungry.

20:48.083 --> 20:49.792
- The thing is, Father,

20:49.792 --> 20:51.792
you can't be harassing
the customers.

20:51.792 --> 20:53.875
Coffin: Mmm, it's God's work,
my dear!

20:53.875 --> 20:56.333
Soon I will have a congregation
to support me.

20:58.917 --> 21:00.750
- Up here, Father.

21:00.750 --> 21:03.167
- Lovely. Ah, such blue eyes.

21:03.167 --> 21:05.292
- You'll need something
to wash that down.

21:05.292 --> 21:06.625
I'll fetch you some water.

21:06.625 --> 21:08.250
- What about ale, Father?

21:08.250 --> 21:09.875
- Oh no, no, no, no I mustn't.

21:09.875 --> 21:12.083
- No, no, no, the Father
is trying to remain sober.

21:12.083 --> 21:14.083
- Oh, it's only a little
alcohol.

21:14.083 --> 21:15.417
It's hardly more than water.

21:15.417 --> 21:17.333
(Ale pours)

21:17.333 --> 21:19.708
(Pitcher clanks,
cup thumps down)

21:19.708 --> 21:21.333
(Low hum of chatter)

21:22.542 --> 21:24.125
(Fire crackles)

21:24.125 --> 21:25.417
- (Inhales)

21:26.625 --> 21:28.958
T-t-t-to wash down the bread.

21:28.958 --> 21:30.458
- Yeah, that's right.

21:30.458 --> 21:32.125
A little sip can't hurt.

21:32.125 --> 21:33.833
- (Gulping) Mmm.

21:40.500 --> 21:42.083
Emberly: Why the hell did
you na warn me?!

21:42.083 --> 21:44.458
Chesterfield: Lord Benton
connected you to the native boy

21:44.458 --> 21:45.458
and came straight to you!

21:45.458 --> 21:48.708
- Well, you should stop him!
Divert him, whatever it takes.

21:48.708 --> 21:50.958
If his men discover this
we're both dead.

21:50.958 --> 21:54.708
- He's just trying to intimidate
you to prove a point.

21:54.708 --> 21:56.667
- Well, this should buy
us some time.

21:56.667 --> 21:58.667
This place hasna been used
in years.

21:58.667 --> 22:00.667
- I'll make sure
it stays that way.

22:00.667 --> 22:02.500
- I hope so,
Captain Chesterfield

22:02.500 --> 22:03.917
because if these pelts
get traced back to me

22:03.917 --> 22:05.625
I will not take the fall alone.

22:06.875 --> 22:08.958
- You think twice before
you threaten me!

22:08.958 --> 22:10.292
(Breathing hard)

22:10.292 --> 22:12.000
- Calm down.

22:12.000 --> 22:14.167
We're in this together.

22:14.167 --> 22:16.583
- Did you have me followed,

22:16.583 --> 22:18.208
when I took the boy, Kitchi?

22:18.208 --> 22:19.458
Did you tell Declan Harp?

22:19.458 --> 22:20.875
- Of course not.

22:20.875 --> 22:22.917
- If you're in league
with Harp...

22:22.917 --> 22:24.833
- Chesterfield,
I'm in league with you

22:24.833 --> 22:27.000
and only you.

22:27.000 --> 22:29.125
I want what you want -

22:29.125 --> 22:30.625
for you to become Governor

22:30.625 --> 22:33.292
and for Benton to disappear.

22:33.292 --> 22:35.125
- (Calming breaths)

22:36.917 --> 22:39.083
I want to believe you, Grace.

22:44.417 --> 22:46.417
- Keep your focus,
Captain Chesterfield.

22:50.125 --> 22:51.708
- Yes, of course.

22:54.292 --> 22:56.458
We have to move
these pelts fast.

22:56.458 --> 22:59.000
We need to find a buyer
in Montreal.

22:59.000 --> 23:01.417
- I'm workin' on it.

23:01.417 --> 23:03.417
You need to steal
the company ledger.

23:03.417 --> 23:05.042
If we don't adjust the numbers

23:05.042 --> 23:07.250
Lord Benton will discover
the theft.

23:07.250 --> 23:09.458
Bring it to me.
I'll deal with the rest.

23:09.458 --> 23:13.083
♪♪♪

23:13.083 --> 23:16.208
- If you're lyin' to me
about Harp,

23:16.208 --> 23:18.500
you'll suffer for it,

23:18.500 --> 23:20.542
you and your girls.

23:20.542 --> 23:25.708
♪♪♪

23:25.708 --> 23:27.458
(Door opens and shuts)

23:31.792 --> 23:34.625
- No? Okay.
- Yeah? Watch it.

23:34.625 --> 23:37.125
- Move. (Puddle splashes)

23:37.125 --> 23:38.667
(Footsteps splash)

23:39.875 --> 23:41.500
(Door squeaks open)

23:42.875 --> 23:44.583
(Door shuts)

23:44.583 --> 23:49.125
♪♪♪

23:49.125 --> 23:50.500
(Fire crackles)

23:50.500 --> 23:52.417
(Wind gusts)

23:52.417 --> 23:54.625
(Footsteps crunch in the snow)

23:57.833 --> 24:00.292
- Fine.

24:00.292 --> 24:03.208
If it'll end these murders

24:03.208 --> 24:05.500
I'll talk to the fuckin'
Lake Walkers.

24:07.250 --> 24:08.583
How do we do this?

24:08.583 --> 24:10.500
- We approach the Okimaw.

24:10.500 --> 24:12.750
We go to her alone and unarmed.

24:12.750 --> 24:14.708
- We could be walkin'
into an ambush.

24:14.708 --> 24:16.292
- She is a woman of honor.

24:16.292 --> 24:17.958
I'll guarantee your safety.

24:17.958 --> 24:20.375
- If anything happens to me,
my men will attack their camp

24:20.375 --> 24:22.417
and take their revenge
and I'll tell her that, too.

24:22.417 --> 24:25.083
- We're going to make peace
not threats, Brown.

24:25.083 --> 24:26.625
(Wind gusts)

24:26.625 --> 24:35.250
♪♪♪

24:35.250 --> 24:37.167
We need to give Sokanon
and Michael time.

24:37.167 --> 24:39.000
You work with his men,

24:39.000 --> 24:40.292
set up a perimeter
around the camp

24:40.292 --> 24:41.792
in case Machk comes back.

24:41.958 --> 24:43.167
I wanna be ready.

24:43.708 --> 24:50.542
♪♪♪

24:50.542 --> 24:52.708
Grant: As you know,
Mr. Carruthers,

24:52.708 --> 24:55.417
there is a vast global demand
for furs.

24:55.417 --> 24:57.458
Prices have never been higher.

24:57.458 --> 24:59.708
Enormous wealth
waiting to be made.

24:59.708 --> 25:01.458
(Glass clanks lightly)

25:01.458 --> 25:03.542
The Hudson's Bay Company
has controlled

25:03.542 --> 25:05.833
the northern trade
for a hundred years

25:05.833 --> 25:08.125
as if this land and its wealth

25:08.125 --> 25:10.000
is their birthright,

25:10.000 --> 25:12.208
but that, sir, is about to end.

25:12.208 --> 25:14.583
We are about to take the
fur trade and make it our own.

25:16.208 --> 25:18.250
Now, I have vast experience,
of course.

25:18.250 --> 25:20.292
I made my fortune
in the Hudson Valley

25:20.292 --> 25:21.708
and I can assure you

25:21.708 --> 25:24.250
that by sharing information,
resources,

25:25.958 --> 25:28.542
and by giving a better price
for pelts,

25:28.542 --> 25:32.000
the Native Tribes will abandon
the glorious HBC

25:32.000 --> 25:34.167
and trade with us and so--

25:34.167 --> 25:38.667
- Does this gentleman ever
fuckin' shut up?

25:38.667 --> 25:40.125
- I beg your pardon?

25:40.125 --> 25:42.500
- I hear that you're in league
with them already, Brown.

25:42.500 --> 25:44.167
Is it true?

25:44.167 --> 25:47.375
Douglas: Mr. Grant has made
a modest investment.

25:47.375 --> 25:50.750
- Because your ship went down,
you had no choice.

25:53.667 --> 25:57.000
Don't mistake me for one
of your American friends.

25:57.000 --> 25:59.458
I don't just bend over
and show you my arse

25:59.458 --> 26:01.417
at the sound of some
pretty words.

26:01.417 --> 26:03.583
- What a shame.

26:03.583 --> 26:06.417
- Perhaps you don't understand
what those words mean--

26:06.417 --> 26:09.500
- Grant, I don't need you
or your money.

26:09.500 --> 26:12.125
I've trade agreements
with Native Tribes.

26:12.125 --> 26:14.792
I have transport,
warehousing, ships,

26:14.792 --> 26:16.958
buyers in London and Paris.

26:16.958 --> 26:19.667
I take raw pelts, I turn them
into the finest garments.

26:19.667 --> 26:21.500
I have it all.

26:21.500 --> 26:24.042
So my advice to you, Mr. Grant,

26:24.042 --> 26:26.583
is you should bugger off
back to New York.

26:26.583 --> 26:27.958
(Slurps)

26:27.958 --> 26:29.958
(Cup bangs down)
(Sucks his thumb)

26:29.958 --> 26:31.458
Good luck to ya, Brown.

26:31.458 --> 26:33.625
You're gonna need it.

26:33.625 --> 26:35.583
(Door opens)
- You're being hasty, Peter.

26:35.583 --> 26:36.875
You should hear him out!

26:36.875 --> 26:38.750
(Door bangs shut)

26:38.750 --> 26:40.542
D-donna be offended.

26:42.083 --> 26:43.417
- Out.

26:43.417 --> 26:46.333
- His manner's a bit--
- (Violent bang) Out!

26:46.333 --> 26:47.792
(Door opens)

26:49.583 --> 26:50.875
(Door shuts)

26:50.875 --> 26:53.125
(Footsteps thud)

26:53.125 --> 26:55.208
- Shh.

26:55.208 --> 26:57.667
The English, so refined.

27:04.833 --> 27:07.458
- You will speak
with Mr. Carruthers...

27:07.458 --> 27:09.958
and you will make him
understand my point of view!

27:09.958 --> 27:11.792
(Violent rattling bangs)

27:17.583 --> 27:18.833
Take Brown with you.

27:18.833 --> 27:20.583
- I don't need any help.

27:21.750 --> 27:24.167
- You may need a witness.

27:25.625 --> 27:27.500
- (Small chuckle)

27:29.833 --> 27:32.167
(Patron singing)
(Cask thumps down)

27:32.167 --> 27:34.500
- Miss Emberly,
Jean-Marc Rivard is here.

27:34.500 --> 27:36.583
(Patrons laugh and chatter)

27:42.667 --> 27:43.833
(Footsteps thud)

27:45.167 --> 27:46.625
(Cups bang down)

27:46.625 --> 27:48.292
- On the house.

27:49.708 --> 27:51.875
- (Slurping gulps) Hmm.

27:51.875 --> 27:54.000
(Cup bangs down) Ah!

27:56.250 --> 27:58.375
I don't suppose you've seen
Declan Harp?

27:58.375 --> 28:00.833
He ask me to do something
for him and then he disappear.

28:00.833 --> 28:03.500
- I didn't ask you here to talk
about Declan Harp.

28:03.500 --> 28:05.042
- No?

28:05.042 --> 28:07.333
- I don't trust you, Rivard,

28:07.333 --> 28:11.000
but it is my belief that
you are entirely for sale.

28:11.000 --> 28:13.208
Your discretion can be bought

28:14.417 --> 28:16.750
and I'm willing to pay you well.

28:20.125 --> 28:22.250
- I don't understand
this conversation.

28:22.250 --> 28:24.458
- I've got a job for you,

28:24.458 --> 28:27.458
but there are rules.
If you tell anyone about it

28:27.458 --> 28:29.542
I've also enough money
to have you killed,

28:29.542 --> 28:32.125
which I suspect wouldna
cost much.

28:32.125 --> 28:35.167
- Normally a woman will
make me dinner

28:35.167 --> 28:37.500
before she threatens
to have me murdered.

28:39.458 --> 28:41.417
- There's a man in Montreal,

28:41.417 --> 28:43.167
an American, Samuel Grant.

28:44.500 --> 28:46.917
I believe you have
his acquaintance?

28:46.917 --> 28:48.750
I want you to deliver
a letter to him

28:48.750 --> 28:50.708
directly into his hands.

28:50.708 --> 28:51.958
- What about?

28:51.958 --> 28:53.833
Why would you need
to write a letter--

28:53.833 --> 28:55.958
(Coins clank loudly)

28:55.958 --> 28:57.292
(Fire crackles)

28:57.292 --> 28:59.542
Hm. You don't pay me
to ask questions.

28:59.542 --> 29:01.500
- That's right.

29:01.500 --> 29:04.958
- I just arrive from Montreal
and now you ask me to go back?

29:04.958 --> 29:06.583
- Would you do it?

29:06.583 --> 29:08.417
- (Sighs)

29:08.417 --> 29:10.042
I assume this is for me?

29:11.917 --> 29:14.042
(Cup scrapes)
- Ah.

29:14.042 --> 29:16.333
(Slurping gulps)

29:19.792 --> 29:21.500
(Cup bangs down) Ah.

29:23.208 --> 29:24.958
(Coins clink and thump down)

29:26.875 --> 29:28.625
- Come see me tomorrow.

29:28.625 --> 29:30.375
I'll give you the letter.

29:30.375 --> 29:32.542
(Receding footsteps)

29:37.250 --> 29:38.958
(Door creaks open, bangs shut)

29:40.333 --> 29:44.292
♪♪♪

29:44.292 --> 29:45.792
(Canvas rustles)

29:45.792 --> 30:00.458
♪♪♪

30:00.458 --> 30:02.208
(Lid clatters)

30:02.208 --> 30:06.292
♪♪♪

30:06.292 --> 30:08.792
- (Labored breathing)

30:08.792 --> 30:11.125
(Footsteps crunch in the snow)

30:11.125 --> 30:12.875
(Weak grunts)

30:15.125 --> 30:16.833
Michael: He hasn't been eatin',

30:16.833 --> 30:19.292
he's lost a lot of blood.

30:19.292 --> 30:21.583
He's not long for this world.

30:21.583 --> 30:24.250
(Panting)

30:24.250 --> 30:28.083
- I never thought you would
survive this long.

30:28.083 --> 30:30.292
- And what do you think now?

30:31.500 --> 30:33.875
- You learn quickly.

30:33.875 --> 30:36.792
I understand why Harp
sees something in you.

30:40.708 --> 30:42.500
And that makes you happy?

30:42.500 --> 30:45.542
♪♪♪

30:45.542 --> 30:48.708
- He's not exactly the easiest
man to please.

30:50.250 --> 30:52.917
- He wasn't always this way.

30:54.750 --> 30:56.167
He had a family.

30:57.500 --> 31:00.167
My sister, Nuna,

31:05.750 --> 31:07.000
he loved her,

31:08.250 --> 31:10.333
they were together.

31:12.833 --> 31:14.208
They had a boy,

31:16.208 --> 31:17.917
Mikinok.

31:19.042 --> 31:26.208
♪♪♪

31:26.208 --> 31:28.042
- What happened?

31:31.458 --> 31:34.292
- She was murdered
by Benton's men,

31:37.000 --> 31:38.958
and their son too.

31:44.583 --> 31:46.500
Their deaths changed him.

31:48.083 --> 31:50.250
He became wild,

31:50.250 --> 31:52.500
dark.

31:52.500 --> 32:04.375
♪♪♪

32:04.375 --> 32:06.458
What he sees in you,

32:07.917 --> 32:09.875
I think it's himself,

32:11.083 --> 32:13.083
who he used to be.

32:13.083 --> 32:18.417
♪♪♪

32:18.417 --> 32:20.542
- Do you think he's right?

32:20.542 --> 32:22.542
♪♪♪

32:22.542 --> 32:23.875
(Twigs snap)

32:25.833 --> 32:27.875
(Footsteps crunch in snow)

32:29.000 --> 32:36.792
♪♪♪

32:36.792 --> 32:38.958
Benton: Now, Imogen,

32:38.958 --> 32:40.875
why do you imagine I have a spy

32:40.875 --> 32:42.625
in the ranks at the ale house?

32:42.625 --> 32:44.417
- (Breathes in to speak)

32:44.417 --> 32:46.917
- So that Grace Emberly
can profit from contraband

32:46.917 --> 32:49.250
behind my back?

32:49.250 --> 32:50.917
- No, m'lord, I...

32:50.917 --> 32:53.833
I didn't recognize
the illegal brandy, I...

32:56.208 --> 32:58.625
- Do you know the name
Threadwell?

32:58.625 --> 33:00.083
- Yes, my Lord.

33:00.083 --> 33:03.417
- Now there's a man
I knew for 32-years,

33:03.417 --> 33:07.417
but when he crossed me
he paid the ultimate price.

33:07.417 --> 33:11.167
So what think you I would do
to a London whore

33:11.167 --> 33:12.917
who crossed me?

33:12.917 --> 33:14.625
(Fire crackles)

33:14.625 --> 33:16.125
- (Breathes shakily)

33:18.417 --> 33:21.125
- Is there anything else
transpiring at the ale house

33:21.125 --> 33:23.500
I should know about?

33:23.500 --> 33:25.750
- No, m'lord.

33:27.708 --> 33:30.083
- And if something
were to arise,

33:31.833 --> 33:33.542
you will report it me directly.

33:34.833 --> 33:36.167
- Yes, m'lord.

33:38.208 --> 33:40.667
I would never lie to you.
I swear.

33:43.500 --> 33:44.833
- Go.

33:44.833 --> 33:46.458
♪♪♪

33:46.458 --> 33:47.625
(Receding footsteps)

33:48.917 --> 33:51.167
(Scrambling footsteps,
birds cawing)

33:51.167 --> 34:00.458
♪♪♪

34:00.458 --> 34:03.625
- You're late, Maclaughlan.

34:03.625 --> 34:06.667
Couple more hours I would
have head back to fort.

34:06.667 --> 34:09.167
You better have a good goddamn
reason for making me wait

34:09.167 --> 34:10.667
in this shit hole.

34:10.667 --> 34:13.375
- He cut my fuckin' ear off!

34:13.375 --> 34:15.708
- Where are your men?
- He killed my fuckin' men!

34:15.708 --> 34:17.083
- Who? Brown?

34:17.083 --> 34:19.375
- No Declan Harp!
- Calm down.

34:20.917 --> 34:22.125
(Fire crackles)

34:23.375 --> 34:25.000
So you're alone?

34:25.000 --> 34:28.000
- Aye, and Harp is a devil,

34:28.958 --> 34:31.125
you knew that,
you fuckin' knew!

34:33.000 --> 34:35.417
- You failed to bring
me Michael Smyth.

34:37.042 --> 34:40.208
Did you at least manage
to stir up some shit

34:40.208 --> 34:42.042
with the Lake Walkers?

34:42.042 --> 34:43.958
- We slit some throats, aye,

34:43.958 --> 34:46.250
and they took the bait.

34:46.250 --> 34:48.417
They think it was Brown,

34:48.417 --> 34:53.042
which means you owe me
some fuckin' money!

34:56.167 --> 34:57.167
(Coins clink)

34:58.333 --> 35:00.292
- Payment in full.

35:00.292 --> 35:01.833
- (Heavy breathing)

35:01.833 --> 35:04.625
You had me kill
the wrong people.

35:04.625 --> 35:07.083
Declan Harp and his people,

35:07.083 --> 35:09.417
they're the bastards
you should worry about!

35:10.875 --> 35:13.250
- And a bonus...

35:13.250 --> 35:15.083
for your trouble.

35:15.083 --> 35:16.375
(Coins clink)

35:19.500 --> 35:22.208
- Least I donna to share
this with anybody.

35:22.208 --> 35:28.208
♪♪♪

35:28.208 --> 35:29.417
- He's been paid.

35:30.583 --> 35:32.750
- Chesterfield.

35:32.750 --> 35:34.667
- Harp was right.

35:34.667 --> 35:36.583
It was Benton
who gave the order.

35:36.583 --> 35:38.292
(Gun cocks)

35:38.292 --> 35:40.208
(Loud boom)
- Michael: Jesus!

35:40.208 --> 35:41.292
(Hard thump)

35:41.292 --> 35:48.292
♪♪♪

35:48.292 --> 35:49.875
(Birds caw)

35:49.875 --> 35:51.583
(Coins clink)

35:51.583 --> 35:53.208
- Let's go!

35:55.083 --> 35:56.667
(Water laps)

35:59.208 --> 36:01.042
- Mr. Grant may ask you
about me.

36:01.042 --> 36:04.292
You will paint him
a favorable portrait.

36:04.292 --> 36:06.583
- Oh, that will be easy.

36:06.583 --> 36:09.417
I will tell him
of your great beauty.

36:09.417 --> 36:12.583
- You will tell him that
I'm a businesswoman,

36:12.583 --> 36:14.958
that I've much to offer.
(Flame sizzles)

36:14.958 --> 36:17.250
If he deals with me
he will prosper.

36:18.625 --> 36:21.292
- Business?

36:21.292 --> 36:24.000
You understand Grant
is a dealer in pelts, furs.

36:27.958 --> 36:30.333
Ah, I'm not being paid
to ask questions.

36:32.292 --> 36:35.042
- For the journey.
It's full of brandy.

36:35.042 --> 36:37.208
- Oh, it might last me
'til supper.

36:37.208 --> 36:39.208
(Chuckles)
(Coins clink)

36:39.208 --> 36:41.667
- Your price.
- Has gone up.

36:41.667 --> 36:44.958
I'll do it, but you must
help me find Declan Harp.

36:48.042 --> 36:49.958
- Deliver this first,

36:49.958 --> 36:52.833
then if I know anything
I'll share it.

36:54.042 --> 36:56.125
If the seal is broken

36:56.125 --> 36:58.542
I will find out
and I will have you--

36:58.542 --> 36:59.917
- You will have me killed.

36:59.917 --> 37:02.167
Yes, uh, I believe you.

37:04.833 --> 37:08.542
Has anyone ever told you
you're a disconcerting woman?

37:08.542 --> 37:10.833
- Bon voyage, Monsieur Rivard.

37:10.833 --> 37:16.917
♪♪♪

37:16.917 --> 37:18.750
(Footsteps crunch in snow)

37:20.250 --> 37:22.208
(Canvas rustles loudly)
- (Breathing hard)

37:22.208 --> 37:23.583
We were right.

37:23.583 --> 37:26.000
He went to a lean-to.
Chesterfield was there.

37:26.000 --> 37:27.917
He paid him and then
he shot him.

37:27.917 --> 37:29.292
- Maclaughlan's dead?

37:29.292 --> 37:31.250
- Chesterfield took
the money back.

37:31.250 --> 37:32.542
- He didn't see you?

37:32.542 --> 37:33.917
- He didn't, and we covered
our tracks.

37:33.917 --> 37:36.708
- Chesterfield? He's the one
that killed Cedric?

37:36.708 --> 37:38.625
- Benton's man.

37:38.625 --> 37:40.458
- He could be the fuckin'
King of England,

37:40.458 --> 37:42.375
I'm still gonna fuckin'
murder him.

37:42.375 --> 37:44.542
- First you're gonna make peace
with Kamenna.

37:44.542 --> 37:46.583
You'll come with us. You'll
tell them what you saw, okay?

37:46.583 --> 37:48.875
Let's go.
Leave your weapons here.

37:48.875 --> 37:51.000
- If Machk is there...
- We go in unarmed.

37:51.000 --> 37:53.375
That's the only way
that this works.

37:53.375 --> 37:55.292
Michael, you and Dimanche
stay in the woods

37:55.292 --> 37:56.667
outside the Lake Walker village

37:56.667 --> 37:58.917
in case Machk or any
of his other boys show up.

37:58.917 --> 38:01.083
You think you can do that,
Dimanche?

38:01.083 --> 38:07.458
♪♪♪

38:07.458 --> 38:10.250
(Patrons laugh
and chatter inside)

38:10.250 --> 38:12.542
(Patrons laugh and chatter
in other room)

38:12.542 --> 38:14.125
(Fire crackles)

38:14.125 --> 38:15.875
(Approaching footsteps)

38:20.417 --> 38:23.208
- Father Coffin'll soon be back
to his former drunken self.

38:23.208 --> 38:25.250
He won't be harassing
the patrons,

38:26.417 --> 38:28.417
we're making sure of it.

38:28.417 --> 38:29.167
(Fire crackles)

38:32.833 --> 38:35.375
For the good of the business.
I thought you'd be pleased.

38:35.375 --> 38:36.417
(Fire crackles)

38:41.792 --> 38:44.500
You have good reason
not to trust me.

38:44.500 --> 38:46.667
I've been spyin'
for Lord Benton.

38:46.667 --> 38:48.708
I can't stop thinking about it

38:48.708 --> 38:50.917
or about how you stood
up to him, before.

38:50.917 --> 38:53.208
It was impressive.

38:53.208 --> 38:55.417
- Flattery now?

38:55.417 --> 38:58.792
- I'm trying to say from now
on I'm on your side.

38:58.792 --> 39:00.625
You can trust me.

39:03.208 --> 39:05.000
- Get back to work.

39:07.500 --> 39:08.500
(Fire crackles)

39:10.083 --> 39:11.417
(Men chatter)

39:17.375 --> 39:20.208
(Door shuts)
(Footsteps thud)

39:22.000 --> 39:23.458
- Carruthers.

39:23.458 --> 39:25.333
- (Sighing heavily)

39:25.333 --> 39:27.375
This had better be good, Brown.

39:27.375 --> 39:29.250
My wife is not amused.

39:30.458 --> 39:32.208
What do you want?

39:32.208 --> 39:33.667
- I'm sorry?

39:33.667 --> 39:36.083
- You sent for me?
What the fuck do you want?

39:36.083 --> 39:38.292
- I didna send for anyone.

39:38.292 --> 39:39.875
(Paper rustles)

39:39.875 --> 39:43.042
- "Come to the offices of the
Low River Company at once."

39:43.042 --> 39:45.042
Douglas Brown.

39:49.167 --> 39:50.917
- I didna write this.

39:52.708 --> 39:55.542
- I did.

39:55.542 --> 39:57.708
I apologize for the deception,

39:57.708 --> 39:59.333
but I needed to see you, sir,

39:59.333 --> 40:03.583
and I was afraid you wouldn't
receive me.

40:03.583 --> 40:07.042
You forgot something at
Mr. Grant's earlier today and...

40:07.042 --> 40:08.917
I wanted to return it to you.

40:10.250 --> 40:12.292
(Chair thuds)

40:12.292 --> 40:13.750
(Cautious footsteps)

40:13.750 --> 40:15.708
(Snickers)

40:15.708 --> 40:17.125
- My pistol.

40:17.125 --> 40:20.042
- Oh, it's a beautiful weapon.

40:20.042 --> 40:22.583
Prussian, isn't it?

40:22.583 --> 40:24.625
And you keep it loaded, yeah?

40:26.000 --> 40:26.875
That's wise.

40:29.417 --> 40:31.375
- That was in my fuckin' office,

40:31.375 --> 40:33.250
locked in my drawer.

40:34.542 --> 40:36.625
How the fuck did you get it?

40:36.625 --> 40:39.417
Douglas: What the hell do you
think you're doin', Pond?

40:39.417 --> 40:41.375
- I'm returning his pistol.

40:44.167 --> 40:45.500
Go on, hmm?

40:47.583 --> 40:48.958
Take it.

40:53.542 --> 40:55.750
(Thunderous bang)
(Hard thud)

40:55.750 --> 40:57.500
- (Panting)

40:59.250 --> 41:00.500
- Hmm.

41:02.292 --> 41:03.625
Oh...

41:05.667 --> 41:07.708
(Blood flowing)

41:07.708 --> 41:09.625
That's gonna be
a closed casket.

41:09.625 --> 41:10.750
- Jesus Christ.

41:12.000 --> 41:14.667
- He tried to shoot me.

41:14.667 --> 41:17.417
I was defending myself.

41:17.417 --> 41:19.167
You're my witness.

41:19.167 --> 41:21.167
- You'll never get away
with this.

41:22.875 --> 41:26.333
- You're gonna have
to clean that up, hm?

41:26.333 --> 41:28.667
Mr. Carruthers has bled
all over your floor.

41:29.792 --> 41:31.667
(Receding footsteps)

41:36.458 --> 41:39.125
(Dog barks, children shout,
men speak in Cree)

41:41.833 --> 41:43.792
(Dogs bark, men speak in Cree)

41:43.792 --> 41:50.125
♪♪♪

41:50.125 --> 41:51.833
Malcolm: What happened
to your people was terrible

41:51.833 --> 41:53.875
and I'm sorry for it,

41:53.875 --> 41:55.333
but I had nothin' to do with it

41:55.333 --> 41:57.458
and anyone who says
I did is a liar.

41:57.458 --> 41:59.375
I'm willin' to put the past
behind me

41:59.375 --> 42:01.208
and look to the future.

42:01.208 --> 42:03.250
I suggest you do the same.

42:03.250 --> 42:05.250
- (Grunts)

42:07.583 --> 42:10.958
- Kamenna, the man who killed
your people,

42:10.958 --> 42:13.083
we followed him to Lord Benton,
to his man.

42:13.083 --> 42:14.667
- You saw this?

42:14.667 --> 42:16.667
- He gave him money.

42:16.667 --> 42:19.167
He paid him to attack your
village and murder your people.

42:19.167 --> 42:21.042
Malcolm: Benton, not me.

42:21.042 --> 42:23.208
- And what of your brother,
Cedric Brown?

42:23.208 --> 42:24.708
Attacking us,

42:25.917 --> 42:28.417
stole my grandson.

42:28.417 --> 42:29.792
Are those lies?

42:29.792 --> 42:31.125
- Now why's she bringin'
that up?

42:31.125 --> 42:33.250
That's got nothin'
to do with this.

42:33.250 --> 42:35.875
My brother did a stupid thing
without my knowledge or consent,

42:35.875 --> 42:37.875
but he paid for it. He's dead,

42:37.875 --> 42:39.458
like my men are dead, all right?

42:39.458 --> 42:41.375
You're not the only one
who's been wronged!

42:41.375 --> 42:42.625
- That's enough.

42:42.625 --> 42:45.667
- Why am I the one
who has to grovel?

42:45.667 --> 42:48.583
- As painful as the death
of my grandson is,

42:48.583 --> 42:51.292
I do wish to look
to the future.

42:53.333 --> 42:55.625
I accept your brother
acted without you.

42:57.417 --> 42:59.917
- Malcolm, you will make amends
for what Cedric did.

42:59.917 --> 43:02.417
Gifts, offerings.

43:02.417 --> 43:05.375
Okimaw, will you accept peace?

43:07.583 --> 43:09.542
(Tent rustles loudly)
- Machk!

43:09.833 --> 43:11.375
You shouldn't be here.

43:11.375 --> 43:12.500
Why not?

43:12.500 --> 43:13.875
This is a peaceful meeting.

43:13.875 --> 43:17.375
You betray our people?
What is this, Kamenna?

43:17.375 --> 43:19.667
Machk: This man killed
our people.

43:19.667 --> 43:21.625
He must die.

43:21.625 --> 43:23.750
- I told you this was
a bad fuckin' idea.

43:23.750 --> 43:26.250
- Our business is with Kamenna,
not with you.

43:26.250 --> 43:28.500
We come unarmed
and in good faith.

43:28.500 --> 43:29.708
We are guests.

43:29.708 --> 43:32.417
- He's right. You have blood
on your hands!

43:32.417 --> 43:35.542
- And you listen to
Declan Harp, not the people!

43:35.542 --> 43:38.083
They demand justice, Kamenna,

43:38.083 --> 43:40.333
and this man, Malcolm Brown,

43:41.417 --> 43:43.875
must pay for what he has done.

43:43.875 --> 43:45.833
(Crunching blow)
- Ah!

43:45.833 --> 43:47.000
- (Grunts)
Sokanon: (Shouts)

43:47.000 --> 43:48.417
- Michael.

43:48.417 --> 43:50.333
- We can't do nothin'.

43:50.333 --> 43:53.083
- No. Harp says we stay here.

43:54.250 --> 43:57.042
Machk: Now we will heal
the land

43:57.042 --> 43:59.083
of this sickness you bring!

43:59.083 --> 44:01.208
Kamenna: These people
are under my protection!

44:01.208 --> 44:03.083
You must not betray that!

44:03.083 --> 44:05.625
Harp: Machk...
(Breathing hard)

44:05.625 --> 44:07.167
let them go.

44:07.167 --> 44:09.417
You and I can settle this
once and for all.

44:09.417 --> 44:12.958
- Why? When I can kill
you all now?

44:12.958 --> 44:14.958
Kamenna: You say the people
are with you.

44:14.958 --> 44:17.042
This is not the way
we make our decisions.

44:17.042 --> 44:19.500
This is a decision for squaw!

44:20.875 --> 44:23.333
You're acting more
like a European!

44:23.333 --> 44:26.750
♪♪♪

44:26.750 --> 44:29.792
If you let them go unharmed,

44:29.792 --> 44:32.875
I'll step aside.
You can be Okimaw.

44:32.875 --> 44:35.333
Harp: Kamenna,
you shouldn't do this.

44:35.333 --> 44:37.708
- I am good to my word.

44:41.125 --> 44:49.583
Let them leave here unharmed.

44:49.583 --> 44:51.958
- As long as I am Okimaw,

44:51.958 --> 44:55.833
I will not allow the stench
of you people near us.

44:56.500 --> 45:00.083
These White People.

45:00.083 --> 45:03.083
Get out.

45:05.583 --> 45:07.250
- You won't be Okimaw for long.

45:07.250 --> 45:16.250
♪♪♪

45:22.167 --> 45:31.167
♪♪♪
